article.description: Alex Morales had a season-high 21 points as Wagner easily defeated Army 82-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Morales scores 21 to carry Wagner past Army 82-62
article.linkText: Morales scores 21 to carry Wagner past Army 82-62
article.story: NEW YORK -- Alex Morales had a season-high 21 points as Wagner easily defeated Army 82-62 on Saturday. Curtis Cobb III had 18 points and eight rebounds for Wagner (3-7), which broke its four-game losing streak. Chase Freeman added 14 points. Alex King had 15 points for the Black Knights (5-6). Lonnie Grayson added 12 points. Josh Caldwell had 10 points and 10 rebounds. Wagner plays Fairfield at home next Saturday. Army faces Bucknell on the road next Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
